name: Anonymous
com:
International football always make me hyped up for Club Football cause I want to see these players on their prime, playing at their absolute peak performance, but I always realize that Club football is just so soulless. Only interesting club football spectacle to watch are UCL knockout stages.
How do we fix it?
The main problem lies in the fact that in all leagues, there are one-two teams that dominate, with EPL being the exception. It's just so boring to see the same team win all the time, while the rest of the teams just pointlessly play against each other for mid table positions.
What's even more sad in European football is that when a team dares to challenge the superiority of the favorite (for example Dortmund against Bayern), the favorite can just buy their best players next season.
You can say what you want about americans, but they have learned how to make their sports interesting and try to make them as competitive as possible with drafts, salary caps, etc. so every team on paper stands a chance to win. There's also play-offs which are exciting and adds more to the intrigue of the competition. Even UCL has become boring with Real Madrid dominating it.
